      <p style="font-weight: bold">*** HEAVILY WORK-IN-PROGRESS ***</p>
      <p>
        Some years ago, an uncanny thing ("Day 1") happened to me.
      </p>
      <h2>Before "Day 1"</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Improved diet, quit smoking</li>
        <li>Sleep-deprived (new baby)</li>
        <li>Increased caffeine consumption</li>
        <li>Involuntary leg jerks</li>
        <li>Crawling/itchy/tingling sensation in the fingers and palms of the
         hands</li>
        <li>Typically sat cross-legged on the sofa of an evening (and had done
         for the past three years)</li>
        <li>
          On one occasion, after consuming alcohol, [somehow] fell asleep
          sitting cross-legged
          <ul>
            <li>Awoke some time later still sitting, head was tilted heavily to
             the right</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>Bruised ego related to an incident in the workplace</li>
        <li>A couple of days illness not immediately prior to the ego-bruising
         event; flu-like symptoms but very short-lived</li>
        <li>No meds.</li>
      </ul>
