         experience (better to have two minds working out WTF was going on than
         just one)</li>
        <li>I have minor recollection of explaining to my line manager what I
         had actually experienced</li>
        <li>Remember talking about possessing the ability to move backwards and
         forwards in time (this was more projection/future prediction, not actual
         physical time travel)</li>
        <li>Talked about how my father was an architect and how he kept
         conceptual models of buildings in his head
          <ul>
	    <li>And how he had to determine where wiring was routed,
             thoroughfares, which direction doors should open, etc.</li>
	    <li>Complying with building regulations, site safety, etc.</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>Requested a few days off which was granted instantly</li>
        <li>Walked slowly back to the car (activity felt effortless)</li>
        <li>Wondered what my wife might say about me returning home from work
